<br>
Nope. I have seen several reports of it being 20%<br>
<br>
And that 20% is applied AFTER the buffs. With nice shaman buffs and 1 level in lifter, a skald should be capable of carrying a ram easily.<br>
<br>
Let me elaborate.<br>
<br>
Weight of a full ram is 236.<br>
<br>
Ram Beak weights 52.<br>
Ram Cladding weights 35.<br>
Swing Harnesses weights 37, need 2, so the total weight is 74.<br>
1 pack of 100 ironwood weights 25, 3 packs weight 75.<br>
<br>
52 + 35 + 37 + 37 + 75 =  236<br>
<br>
Add weight of yer regular equippment, say 44 to make a nice round figure. Total encumberance 280.<br>
<br>
To get 280 with lvl 1 lifter, you would need str 234 (234 x 1.2 = 280.8)  <br>
<br>
Good portion of that 234 can come from shaman buffs. You don't need all that highlevel shaman either.<br>
<br>
Shaman aug baseline lvl 25 str buff yields +39 str<br>
Shaman aug specline lvl 19 str/con buff yields +42 str<br>
<br>
With both these buffs, one would need unbuffed str 153 to carry a full ram. Easily achieveable with all those +str items.<br>
<br>
Never mind shamen. With a lifter, troll thanes can carry a ram with self buffs only.<br>
<br>
To sum it up, lifter is truly a godsend. Logistictics of large scale siege operations was a nightmare (in 1.45 we are still playing on euro servers, ram needs 600 wood, not 300). This nightmare will be no more.<br>
<br>
